{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Let me talk about India"},{"time":2000,"text":"through the evolution of ideas."},{"time":4000,"text":"Now I believe this is an interesting way of looking at it"},{"time":7000,"text":"because in every society, especially an open democratic society,"},{"time":11000,"text":"it's only when ideas take root that things change."},{"time":14000,"text":"Slowly ideas lead to ideology,"},{"time":16000,"text":"lead to policies that lead to actions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":19000,"text":"In 1930 this country went through a Great Depression,"},{"time":22000,"text":"which led to all the ideas of the state and social security,"},{"time":25000,"text":"and all the other things that happened in Roosevelt's time."},{"time":28000,"text":"In the 1980s we had the Reagan revolution, which lead to deregulation."},{"time":31000,"text":"And today, after the global economic crisis,"},{"time":34000,"text":"there was a whole new set of rules"},{"time":36000,"text":"about how the state should intervene."},{"time":38000,"text":"So ideas change states."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40000,"text":"And I looked at India and said,"},{"time":42000,"text":"really there are four kinds of ideas"},{"time":44000,"text":"which really make an impact on India."},{"time":46000,"text":"The first, to my mind,"},{"time":48000,"text":"is what I call as \"the ideas that have arrived.\""},{"time":51000,"text":"These ideas have brought together something"},{"time":53000,"text":"which has made India happen the way it is today."},{"time":56000,"text":"The second set of ideas I call \"ideas in progress.\""},{"time":59000,"text":"Those are ideas which have been accepted"},{"time":62000,"text":"but not implemented yet."},{"time":64000,"text":"The third set of ideas are what I call as"},{"time":66000,"text":"\"ideas that we argue about\" --"},{"time":68000,"text":"those are ideas where we have a fight,"},{"time":70000,"text":"an ideological battle about how to do things."},{"time":73000,"text":"And the fourth thing, which I believe is most important, is"},{"time":76000,"text":"\"the ideas that we need to anticipate.\""},{"time":78000,"text":"Because when you are a developing country"},{"time":80000,"text":"in the world where you can see the problems that other countries are having,"},{"time":84000,"text":"you can actually anticipate"},{"time":86000,"text":"what that did and do things very differently."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89000,"text":"Now in India's case I believe there are six ideas"},{"time":92000,"text":"which are responsible for where it has come today."},{"time":94000,"text":"The first is really the notion of people."},{"time":98000,"text":"In the '60s and '70s"},{"time":100000,"text":"we thought of people as a burden."},{"time":102000,"text":"We thought of people as a liability."},{"time":105000,"text":"Today we talk of people as an asset."},{"time":107000,"text":"We talk of people as human capital."},{"time":110000,"text":"And I believe this change in the mindset,"},{"time":112000,"text":"of looking at people as something of a burden"},{"time":114000,"text":"to human capital,"},{"time":116000,"text":"has been one of the fundamental changes in the Indian mindset."},{"time":119000,"text":"And this change in thinking of human capital"},{"time":121000,"text":"is linked to the fact"},{"time":123000,"text":"that India is going through a demographic dividend."},{"time":126000,"text":"As healthcare improves,"},{"time":128000,"text":"as infant mortality goes down,"},{"time":130000,"text":"fertility rates start dropping. And India is experiencing that."},{"time":133000,"text":"India is going to have"},{"time":135000,"text":"a lot of young people with a demographic dividend"},{"time":138000,"text":"for the next 30 years."},{"time":140000,"text":"What is unique about this demographic dividend"},{"time":142000,"text":"is that India will be the only country in the world"},{"time":145000,"text":"to have this demographic dividend."},{"time":147000,"text":"In other words, it will be the only young country in an aging world."},{"time":151000,"text":"And this is very important. At the same time"},{"time":154000,"text":"if you peel away the demographic dividend in India,"},{"time":156000,"text":"there are actually two demographic curves."},{"time":158000,"text":"One is in the south and in the west of India,"},{"time":161000,"text":"which is already going to be fully expensed by 2015,"},{"time":165000,"text":"because in that part of the country, the fertility rate is"},{"time":168000,"text":"almost equal to that of a West European country."},{"time":171000,"text":"Then there is the whole northern India,"},{"time":174000,"text":"which is going to be the bulk of the future demographic dividend."},{"time":177000,"text":"But a demographic dividend is only as good"},{"time":180000,"text":"as the investment in your human capital."},{"time":183000,"text":"Only if the people have education,"},{"time":185000,"text":"they have good health, they have infrastructure,"},{"time":187000,"text":"they have roads to go to work, they have lights to study at night --"},{"time":190000,"text":"only in those cases can you really get the benefit"},{"time":193000,"text":"of a demographic dividend."},{"time":195000,"text":"In other words, if you don't really invest in the human capital,"},{"time":198000,"text":"the same demographic dividend"},{"time":200000,"text":"can be a demographic disaster."},{"time":202000,"text":"Therefore India is at a critical point"},{"time":204000,"text":"where either it can leverage its demographic dividend"},{"time":207000,"text":"or it can lead to a demographic disaster."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210000,"text":"The second thing in India has been the change in"},{"time":212000,"text":"the role of entrepreneurs."},{"time":214000,"text":"When India got independence entrepreneurs were seen"},{"time":217000,"text":"as a bad lot, as people who would exploit."},{"time":220000,"text":"But today, after 60 years, because of the rise of entrepreneurship,"},{"time":223000,"text":"entrepreneurs have become role models,"},{"time":225000,"text":"and they are contributing hugely to the society."},{"time":228000,"text":"This change has contributed"},{"time":230000,"text":"to the vitality and the whole economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234000,"text":"The third big thing I believe that has changed India"},{"time":236000,"text":"is our attitude towards the English language."},{"time":239000,"text":"English language was seen as a language of the imperialists."},{"time":242000,"text":"But today, with globalization,"},{"time":244000,"text":"with outsourcing, English has become a language of aspiration."},{"time":248000,"text":"This has made it something that everybody wants to learn."},{"time":250000,"text":"And the fact that we have English is now becoming"},{"time":253000,"text":"a huge strategic asset."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255000,"text":"The next thing is technology."},{"time":258000,"text":"Forty years back, computers were seen"},{"time":261000,"text":"as something which was forbidding, something which was intimidating,"},{"time":264000,"text":"something that reduced jobs."},{"time":266000,"text":"Today we live in a country"},{"time":268000,"text":"which sells eight million mobile phones a month,"},{"time":271000,"text":"of which 90 percent of those mobile phones"},{"time":273000,"text":"are prepaid phones"},{"time":275000,"text":"because people don't have credit history."},{"time":277000,"text":"Forty percent of those prepaid phones"},{"time":280000,"text":"are recharged at less than 20 cents at each recharge."},{"time":284000,"text":"That is the scale at which"},{"time":286000,"text":"technology has liberated and made it accessible."},{"time":289000,"text":"And therefore technology has gone"},{"time":291000,"text":"from being seen as something forbidding"},{"time":293000,"text":"and intimidating to something that is empowering."},{"time":296000,"text":"Twenty years back,"},{"time":298000,"text":"when there was a report on bank computerization,"},{"time":300000,"text":"they didn't name the report as"},{"time":303000,"text":"a report on computers,"},{"time":305000,"text":"they call them as \"ledger posting machines.\""},{"time":307000,"text":"They didn't want the unions to believe that they were actually computers."},{"time":310000,"text":"And when they wanted to have more advanced, more powerful computers"},{"time":314000,"text":"they called them \"advanced ledger posting machines.\""},{"time":317000,"text":"So we have come a long way from those days"},{"time":319000,"text":"where the telephone has become an instrument of empowerment,"},{"time":322000,"text":"and really has changed the way Indians think of technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326000,"text":"And then I think the other point"},{"time":328000,"text":"is that Indians today are far more"},{"time":330000,"text":"comfortable with globalization."},{"time":333000,"text":"Again, after having lived for more than 200 years"},{"time":336000,"text":"under the East India Company and under imperial rule,"},{"time":339000,"text":"Indians had a very natural reaction towards globalization"},{"time":343000,"text":"believing it was a form of imperialism."},{"time":345000,"text":"But today, as Indian companies go abroad,"},{"time":347000,"text":"as Indians come and work all over the world,"},{"time":349000,"text":"Indians have gained a lot more confidence"},{"time":351000,"text":"and have realized that globalization is something they can participate in."},{"time":355000,"text":"And the fact that the demographics are in our favor,"},{"time":358000,"text":"because we are the only young country in an aging world,"},{"time":360000,"text":"makes globalization all the more attractive to Indians."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363000,"text":"And finally, India has had"},{"time":366000,"text":"the deepening of its democracy."},{"time":368000,"text":"When democracy came to India 60 years back"},{"time":370000,"text":"it was an elite concept."},{"time":372000,"text":"It was a bunch of people who wanted to bring in democracy"},{"time":375000,"text":"because they wanted to bring in the idea of"},{"time":377000,"text":"universal voting and parliament and constitution and so forth."},{"time":381000,"text":"But today democracy has become a bottom-up process"},{"time":384000,"text":"where everybody has realized"},{"time":386000,"text":"the benefits of having a voice,"},{"time":388000,"text":"the benefits of being in an open society."},{"time":391000,"text":"And therefore democracy has become embedded."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393000,"text":"I believe these six factors --"},{"time":395000,"text":"the rise of the notion of population as human capital,"},{"time":398000,"text":"the rise of Indian entrepreneurs,"},{"time":400000,"text":"the rise of English as a language of aspiration,"},{"time":402000,"text":"technology as something empowering,"},{"time":404000,"text":"globalization as a positive factor,"},{"time":407000,"text":"and the deepening of democracy -- has contributed"},{"time":409000,"text":"to why India is today growing"},{"time":411000,"text":"at rates it has never seen before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413000,"text":"But having said that,"},{"time":415000,"text":"then we come to what I call as ideas in progress."},{"time":417000,"text":"Those are the ideas where there is no argument in a society,"},{"time":420000,"text":"but you are not able to implement those things."},{"time":423000,"text":"And really there are four things here."},{"time":425000,"text":"One is the question of education."},{"time":427000,"text":"For some reason, whatever reason -- lack of money,"},{"time":429000,"text":"lack of priorities, because of religion having an older culture --"},{"time":433000,"text":"primary education was never given the focus it required."},{"time":436000,"text":"But now I believe it's reached a point"},{"time":438000,"text":"where it has become very important."},{"time":440000,"text":"Unfortunately the government schools don't function,"},{"time":443000,"text":"so children are going to private schools today."},{"time":445000,"text":"Even in the slums of India"},{"time":447000,"text":"more than 50 percent of urban kids are going into private schools."},{"time":450000,"text":"So there is a big challenge in getting the schools to work."},{"time":453000,"text":"But having said that, there is an enormous desire"},{"time":455000,"text":"among everybody, including the poor, to educate their children."},{"time":458000,"text":"So I believe primary education is an idea"},{"time":460000,"text":"which is arrived but not yet implemented."}]},{"cues":[{"time":463000,"text":"Similarly, infrastructure --"},{"time":465000,"text":"for a long time, infrastructure was not a priority."},{"time":468000,"text":"Those of you who have been to India have seen that."},{"time":470000,"text":"It's certainly not like China."},{"time":471000,"text":"But today I believe finally infrastructure is something"},{"time":474000,"text":"which is agreed upon and which people want to implement."},{"time":477000,"text":"It is reflected in the political statements."},{"time":480000,"text":"20 years back the political slogan was, \"Roti, kapada, makaan,\""},{"time":484000,"text":"which meant, \"Food, clothing and shelter.\""},{"time":487000,"text":"And today's political slogan is, \"Bijli, sadak, pani,\""},{"time":491000,"text":"which means \"Electricity, water and roads.\""},{"time":493000,"text":"And that is a change in the mindset"},{"time":495000,"text":"where infrastructure is now accepted."},{"time":497000,"text":"So I do believe this is an idea which has arrived,"},{"time":499000,"text":"but simply not implemented."}]},{"cues":[{"time":501000,"text":"The third thing is again cities."},{"time":504000,"text":"It's because Gandhi believed in villages"},{"time":506000,"text":"and because the British ruled from the cities,"},{"time":508000,"text":"therefore Nehru thought of New Delhi as an un-Indian city."},{"time":512000,"text":"For a long time we have neglected our cities."},{"time":515000,"text":"And that is reflected in the kinds of situations that you see."},{"time":518000,"text":"But today, finally, after economic reforms,"},{"time":520000,"text":"and economic growth,"},{"time":522000,"text":"I think the notion that cities are engines"},{"time":524000,"text":"of economic growth,"},{"time":526000,"text":"cities are engines of creativity,"},{"time":528000,"text":"cities are engines of innovation,"},{"time":530000,"text":"have finally been accepted."},{"time":532000,"text":"And I think now you're seeing the move towards improving our cities."},{"time":534000,"text":"Again, an idea which is arrived, but not yet implemented."}]},{"cues":[{"time":538000,"text":"The final thing is the notion of India as a single market --"},{"time":542000,"text":"because when you didn't think of India as a market,"},{"time":544000,"text":"you didn't really bother about a single market, because it didn't really matter."},{"time":547000,"text":"And therefore you had a situation"},{"time":549000,"text":"where every state had its own market for products."},{"time":552000,"text":"Every province had its own market for agriculture."},{"time":555000,"text":"Increasingly now the policies of"},{"time":557000,"text":"taxation and infrastructure and all that,"},{"time":559000,"text":"are moving towards creating India as a single market."},{"time":562000,"text":"So there is a form of internal globalization which is happening,"},{"time":565000,"text":"which is as important as external globalization."},{"time":568000,"text":"These four factors I believe --"},{"time":570000,"text":"the ones of primary education,"},{"time":572000,"text":"infrastructure, urbanization, and single market --"},{"time":575000,"text":"in my view are ideas in India"},{"time":577000,"text":"which have been accepted, but not implemented."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581000,"text":"Then we have what I believe are the ideas in conflict."},{"time":584000,"text":"The ideas that we argue about."},{"time":587000,"text":"These are the arguments we have which cause gridlock."},{"time":590000,"text":"What are those ideas? One is, I think, are ideological issues."},{"time":594000,"text":"Because of the historical Indian background, in the caste system,"},{"time":598000,"text":"and because of the fact that there have been many people"},{"time":600000,"text":"who have been left out in the cold,"},{"time":602000,"text":"a lot of the politics is about how to make sure"},{"time":604000,"text":"that we'll address that."},{"time":606000,"text":"And it leads to reservations and other techniques."},{"time":609000,"text":"It's also related to the way that we subsidize our people,"},{"time":611000,"text":"and all the left and right arguments that we have."},{"time":615000,"text":"A lot of the Indian problems are related to the ideology"},{"time":618000,"text":"of caste and other things."},{"time":620000,"text":"This policy is causing gridlock."},{"time":622000,"text":"This is one of the factors which needs to be resolved."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625000,"text":"The second one is the labor policies that we have,"},{"time":628000,"text":"which make it so difficult for"},{"time":630000,"text":"entrepreneurs to create standardized jobs in companies,"},{"time":634000,"text":"that 93 percent of Indian labor"},{"time":636000,"text":"is in the unorganized sector."},{"time":638000,"text":"They have no benefits: they don't have social security;"},{"time":641000,"text":"they don't have pension; they don't have healthcare; none of those things."},{"time":644000,"text":"This needs to be fixed because unless you can bring these people"},{"time":646000,"text":"into the formal workforce,"},{"time":648000,"text":"you will end up creating a whole lot of people who are completely disenfranchised."},{"time":652000,"text":"Therefore we need to create a new set of labor laws,"},{"time":655000,"text":"which are not as onerous as they are today."},{"time":659000,"text":"At the same time give a policy for a lot more people to be in the formal sector,"},{"time":663000,"text":"and create the jobs for the millions of people that we need to create jobs for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":666000,"text":"The third thing is our higher education."},{"time":669000,"text":"Indian higher education is completely regulated."},{"time":672000,"text":"It's very difficult to start a private university."},{"time":675000,"text":"It's very difficult for a foreign university to come to India."},{"time":678000,"text":"As a result of that our higher education"},{"time":680000,"text":"is simply not keeping pace with India's demands."},{"time":683000,"text":"That is leading to a lot of problems which we need to address."}]},{"cues":[{"time":687000,"text":"But most important I believe"},{"time":689000,"text":"are the ideas we need to anticipate."},{"time":691000,"text":"Here India can look at what is happening in the west"},{"time":693000,"text":"and elsewhere, and look at what needs to be done."},{"time":696000,"text":"The first thing is, we're very fortunate"},{"time":698000,"text":"that technology is at a point"},{"time":700000,"text":"where it is much more advanced"},{"time":702000,"text":"than when other countries had the development."},{"time":704000,"text":"So we can use technology for governance."},{"time":706000,"text":"We can use technology for direct benefits."},{"time":708000,"text":"We can use technology for transparency, and many other things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711000,"text":"The second thing is, the health issue."},{"time":713000,"text":"India has equally horrible"},{"time":715000,"text":"health problems of the higher state of cardiac issue,"},{"time":718000,"text":"the higher state of diabetes, the higher state of obesity."},{"time":721000,"text":"So there is no point in replacing a set of poor country diseases"},{"time":724000,"text":"with a set of rich country diseases."},{"time":727000,"text":"Therefore we're to rethink the whole way we look at health."},{"time":730000,"text":"We really need to put in place a strategy"},{"time":732000,"text":"so that we don't go to the other extreme of health."}]},{"cues":[{"time":735000,"text":"Similarly today in the West"},{"time":737000,"text":"you're seeing the problem of entitlement --"},{"time":739000,"text":"the cost of social security, the cost of Medicare, the cost of Medicaid."},{"time":743000,"text":"Therefore when you are a young country,"},{"time":745000,"text":"again you have a chance to put in place a modern pension system"},{"time":748000,"text":"so that you don't create entitlement problems as you grow old."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752000,"text":"And then again, India does not have the luxury"},{"time":755000,"text":"of making its environment dirty,"},{"time":757000,"text":"because it has to marry environment and development."},{"time":761000,"text":"Just to give an idea, the world has to stabilize"},{"time":764000,"text":"at something like 20 gigatons per year."},{"time":767000,"text":"On a population of nine billion"},{"time":769000,"text":"our average carbon emission will have to be about two tons per year."},{"time":772000,"text":"India is already at two tons per year."},{"time":774000,"text":"But if India grows at something like eight percent,"},{"time":777000,"text":"income per year per person will go to 16 times by 2050."},{"time":781000,"text":"So we're saying: income growing at 16 times and no growth in carbon."},{"time":785000,"text":"Therefore we will fundamentally rethink the way we look at the environment,"},{"time":788000,"text":"the way we look at energy,"},{"time":790000,"text":"the way we create whole new paradigms of development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":794000,"text":"Now why does this matter to you?"},{"time":797000,"text":"Why does what's happening 10 thousand miles away matter to all of you?"},{"time":801000,"text":"Number one, this matters because"},{"time":804000,"text":"this represents more than a billion people."},{"time":807000,"text":"A billion people, 1/6th of the world population."},{"time":810000,"text":"It matters because this is a democracy."},{"time":813000,"text":"And it is important to prove"},{"time":815000,"text":"that growth and democracy are not incompatible,"},{"time":818000,"text":"that you can have a democracy, that you can have an open society,"},{"time":821000,"text":"and you can have growth."},{"time":823000,"text":"It's important because if you solve these problems,"},{"time":826000,"text":"you can solve the problems of poverty in the world."},{"time":828000,"text":"It's important because"},{"time":830000,"text":"you need it to solve the world's environment problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":832000,"text":"If we really want to come to a point,"},{"time":834000,"text":"we really want to put a cap on our carbon emission,"},{"time":836000,"text":"we want to really lower the use of energy --"},{"time":839000,"text":"it has to be solved in countries like India."},{"time":842000,"text":"You know if you look at the development"},{"time":844000,"text":"in the West over 200 years,"},{"time":846000,"text":"the average growth may have been about two percent."},{"time":849000,"text":"Here we are talking about countries growing at eight to nine percent."},{"time":852000,"text":"And that makes a huge difference."},{"time":854000,"text":"When India was growing at about three, 3.5 percent"},{"time":858000,"text":"and the population was growing at two percent,"},{"time":861000,"text":"its per capita income was doubling every 45 years."},{"time":865000,"text":"When the economic growth goes to eight percent"},{"time":868000,"text":"and population growth drops to 1.5 percent,"},{"time":871000,"text":"then per capita income is doubling every nine years."},{"time":874000,"text":"In other words, you're certainly fast-forwarding this whole process"},{"time":877000,"text":"of a billion people going to prosperity."},{"time":880000,"text":"And you must have a clear strategy"},{"time":882000,"text":"which is important for India and important for the world."},{"time":885000,"text":"That is why I think all of you"},{"time":887000,"text":"should be equally concerned with it as I am."},{"time":889000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":891000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}